		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">RG59 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The wiki says $0D may cause problems for some TVs and should not be used. What exactly happens?</div><br />Some TVs confuse it for a sync signal. This can cause the picture to flicker, jump, roll, or just go blank (if the TV blanks unrecognized signals).

		

